dataIdInfo.idPurp: Provides the location of stream gages in the Albuquerque District.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: USGS streamgages within the Albuquerque District boundary. Stream gages measure water elevation in drainage (stream) channels. The elevation is converted to stream flow to calculate and monitor the amount of water flowing through a channel. The gages are subdivided into 3 types, Status=Active and Record=Continuous, Status=Active and Record=Partial, and Status=Inactive. Stream gages measure the water elevation in drainage channels. The stream gage locations were downloaded from the National Hydrography Dataset (NHD) as a geodatabase, NHDPointEvents_fgdb, from http://nhd.usgs.gov/ (ftp://nhdftp.usgs.gov/DataSets/National/) and converted from an event feature class to shapefile.
